Copper Blues is one of my favorite Cityscape spots.
A great venue for live music and great beer selection.
Whenever I have a planned night out downtown I check the music calendar and if EastonAshe is in the house I make sure to stop in.
They play here often and they're one of my favorite, rockin' Phoenix cover bands.
It can get crowded when the bands playing but the outdoor patio is usually a little less crowded so you can at least step out there to get away from the crowd, if needed.
We were offered penny pint tickets on the way in and that was a big score!
I'm sure the bartenders love those deals as well.
We definitely tip more when the drink is pretty much free!

