Copper Blues was a lot of fun.
The night I was there they did not have a live band but were playing tons of good music.
The place was spacious enough to move around without being up in someone's grill.
The downside was that when a comedy show let out, there was a mad rush to the bar, and it took forever to get your drinks.
That being said, -- being next door to Stand Up Live is awesome.
